{
    "title": "There are 2 popular docker images for Apache Kafka: Wurstmeister and Bitnami",
    "paragraphs": [
{
        "text": "Download this zip and unpack it under an directory les01",
        "code": {
            "language": "zip",
            "path": "./data/les01/les01.zip"
        }},
     
        {
            "text": "And from now on you can start Apache Kafka",
            "code": {
                "code": "docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml up"
            },
            "conclusion": "with Ctrl-C you can stop Apache Kafka"
        },
        {
            "text": "Or start Apache Kafka in detached mode (preferred):",
            "code": {
                "code": "docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml up -d"
            }
        },
        {
            "text": "And stop Apache Kafka with: ",
            "code": {
                "code": "docker-compose  -f docker-compose.yml stop"
            }
        },
        {
            "text": "And start Apache Kafka again",
            "code": {
                "code": "docker-compose  -f docker-compose.yml start"
            }
        },
        {
            "text": "Also you should be able to use Kafka by logging in into the running Kafka Image and do basic operations. See last 5 minutes Bitnami video. ",
            "code": {
                "code": "docker exec -it kafka /bin/sh"
            }
        },
       
        {
            "text": "The code for wurstmeister",
            "code": {
                "language": "yml",
                "path": "./data/les01/docker-compose-wurstmeister.yml"
            }
        },
        {
            "text": "Optional a popular Kafka Manager made by yahoo",
            "code": {
                "language": "txt",
                "path": "./data/les01/README.txt"
            }
        },
        {
            "text": "And later to start a cluster with 3 brokers",
            "code": {
                "language": "cmd",
                "path": "./data/les01/runthiscommandfor3brokers.cmd"
            }
        }

    ]
}